1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:06,640
Are you the armpit stand-in?

2
00:00:06,680 --> 00:00:07,840
- Yes, I am.
- Whoa.

3
00:00:07,880 --> 00:00:10,680
Win Pawee?

4
00:00:11,280 --> 00:00:12,960
When did you get back to Thailand?

5
00:00:12,960 --> 00:00:14,640
How is it, Win? Like the house?

6
00:00:14,640 --> 00:00:16,800
Why did you move in so fast?

7
00:00:19,560 --> 00:00:22,000
So Win Pawee is the one who bought this house?

8
00:00:24,280 --> 00:00:26,240
Does this house have some kind of history?

9
00:00:26,280 --> 00:00:28,600
I feel like something’s off.

10
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:48,800
Win, why do you look like
you haven’t slept at all?

11
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:50,440
Yeah, I didn’t sleep all night.

12
00:00:50,480 --> 00:00:52,240
This house has a ghost.

13
00:00:59,520 --> 00:01:00,800
Tom, why did you invite a monk?

14
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:03,000
You were the one who said
this house has a ghost.

15
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:04,640
This is a straight-to-the-point solution.

16
00:01:04,640 --> 00:01:06,840
Okay, that’s funny.
Inviting monk...

17
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:13,440
Amen, Luang Por.

18
00:01:13,640 --> 00:01:15,440
You don’t have to bless me that much.

19
00:01:15,920 --> 00:01:17,320
Inside the house is fine.

20
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:24,840
Luang Por.

21
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:26,720
The kitchen would be better.

22
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:28,000
The scene of the incident.

23
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:34,080
Luang Por.

24
00:01:34,120 --> 00:01:36,440
Right here is good.
Where it happened.

25
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:39,280
Please bless everywhere.

26
00:01:41,520 --> 00:01:43,320
Since we’re at it anyway,

27
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:45,720
could you do that room too?

28
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:57,440
This room too.

29
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:23,320
That room over there as well, Luang Por.

30
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:36,400
Don’t forget under the bed too, Luang Por.

31
00:02:36,440 --> 00:02:38,320
Ghosts like hiding under beds.

32
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:43,000
Tom, don’t talk like that.

33
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:45,920
I’m serious. Haven’t you watched movies?

34
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:50,440
Then please really focus, Luang Por.

35
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:04,640
A…men. This way, please.

36
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:24,720
A…men.

37
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:28,920
Singing competition today.

38
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:31,400
Feeling lucky.

39
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:34,320
Might get through without even trying.

40
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:18,520
- Hey there.
- I’m ready.

41
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:20,720
Great. Go ahead.

42
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:33,520
Hello, my name is Miss Wanneung.

43
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:35,120
- Rojana…
- You can start singing.

44
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,320
Okay.

45
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:48,320
Okay, that’s enough.

46
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:51,000
I’ve only sung a few words.

47
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,200
Thank you. Come back again next year.

48
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:55,280
I came last year too.

49
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:57,800
And you said the exact same thing.

50
00:05:57,840 --> 00:05:59,640
Please, just a little more.

51
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:03,840
That’s enough. Please leave.

52
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:54,920
How am I supposed to get into the house?

53
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:18,520
Why aren’t you going to bed yet?

54
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:20,720
I’m already so sleepy.

55
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:36,640
You.

56
00:08:36,800 --> 00:08:37,800
You.

57
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:39,280
Give me your hand.

58
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:40,720
Give me your hand.

59
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,920
Hold my hand.

60
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:50,240
Help!

61
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:02,360
- You’re okay now.
- Help! Help!

62
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:03,400
Hey.

63
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:05,640
Hey.

64
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:09,040
Please help me.

65
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:10,600
Easy, okay?

66
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:14,240
You’re safe now.

67
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,400
Calm down.

68
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:22,440
You’re safe.

69
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,920
Win Pawee.

70
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:32,680
Win Pawee.

71
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:35,000
Can I take a selfie with you?

72
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:36,920
I really like you...

73
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:44,920
You again?

74
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:47,920
You followed me all the way home?

75
00:09:50,240 --> 00:09:52,040
- Well…
- You’re a sasaeng, right?

76
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:54,480
How did you get into my house?
What do you want?

77
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:56,640
Photos? Or digging up my secrets?

78
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:58,120
Well...

79
00:09:58,160 --> 00:10:00,840
- I…
- If you don’t tell me, I’ll call the police.

80
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:03,440
Hey you, what would you report me for?

81
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:06,640
Breaking into someone’s house without permission.

82
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:11,200
I’m not a sasaeng.
I’m nothing like that.

83
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:13,400
This is my house.

84
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:14,640
Your house?

85
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:16,880
Don’t lie and make things up.

86
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:18,880
You own a house with a pool,

87
00:10:18,920 --> 00:10:20,120
but you can’t even swim?

88
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:22,680
When I was a kid, I fell into the water.

89
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:25,080
Right here. In this pool.

90
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:27,600
So I ended up with a fear of swimming.

91
00:10:27,640 --> 00:10:28,800
Isn’t it true

92
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:32,120
that you’ve been following me
since the mall the other day?

93
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:34,120
Do you know this is illegal?

94
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:35,280
I’m calling…

95
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:37,000
It’s not like that.

96
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:39,440
This really is my house.

97
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:41,520
- I don’t care anymore.
- Win Pawee.

98
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:44,600
Do you know how much
this house means to me?

99
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:47,440
I was born here.
I grew up here.

100
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:50,400
Look at this wall.

101
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:54,440
It’s my very first abstract piece ever.

102
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:57,440
Look at that.

103
00:10:57,720 --> 00:11:01,280
When I was a kid, I kicked a ball
and it bounced into it.

104
00:11:01,320 --> 00:11:03,080
Look at my progress.

105
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:05,480
From when I was this short,

106
00:11:05,520 --> 00:11:07,920
to this tall now.

107
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:11,800
That’s how much this house means to me.

108
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:12,840
You really…

109
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:14,640
were short since you were a kid, huh?

110
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:19,520
I’m not short.

111
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:27,240
Hey.

112
00:11:27,240 --> 00:11:28,840
Don’t let go of me.

113
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:31,480
If you don’t want me to call the police,

114
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:33,280
then get out of my house right now.

115
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:35,920
I’m not leaving. I’ll stay.

116
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:37,120
One.

117
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:40,880
I love this place.
This is my home.

118
00:11:40,920 --> 00:11:41,920
Two.

119
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:43,400
If you want me gone,

120
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:45,000
then kill me instead.

121
00:11:45,040 --> 00:11:46,720
- Three.
- Hey.

122
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:49,240
Please let me stay here.

123
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:50,520
Get out. Now.

124
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:54,720
- Hey… so I can stay, right?
- Are you serious?

125
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:56,960
- Get out.
- No.

126
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:58,040
No.

127
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:04,720
Hey.

128
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:07,080
Wait. Just listen to me first.

129
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:10,000
I really am the owner of this house.

130
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:12,240
Hey.

131
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:13,720
Hey.

132
00:13:19,520 --> 00:13:20,520
Win.

133
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:22,640
It’s May.

134
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:25,120
Sorry for calling so late.

135
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:27,320
Where did you get my number?

136
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:29,920
I asked your mom for it.

137
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:32,840
Why did you bother my mom?

138
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:37,640
If you have something to say, say it fast.
It’s late. I’m going to bed.

139
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:40,040
I just miss you.

140
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:41,920
I wanted to talk to you.

141
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,240
And…

142
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:45,240
I wanted to tell you that

143
00:13:45,320 --> 00:13:47,600
right now, I’m all alone.

144
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:50,640
No one can stop our love anymore, Win.

145
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:52,840
Let’s get back…

146
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:55,040
May?

147
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:56,720
What’s wrong, May?

148
00:13:58,040 --> 00:13:59,080
Hello?

149
00:13:59,120 --> 00:14:01,320
May, answer me. May?

150
00:14:28,720 --> 00:14:30,920
Should I sneak into the house again?

151
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:34,480
But if he actually calls the police,

152
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:35,840
what am I supposed to do?

153
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:39,640
That could totally end my career
in entertainment.

154
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:05,920
Could you be a little gentler?

155
00:15:05,920 --> 00:15:08,120
Sorry, it needs to be wrapped pretty tight.

156
00:15:11,560 --> 00:15:12,920
All set.

157
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:16,000
Next time, you really need
to be more careful.

158
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:19,520
Don’t just stand on the roadside
talking on the phone like that.

159
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,280
You could get hit by a motorbike.

160
00:15:21,320 --> 00:15:23,040
You’re lucky it’s just your ankle.

161
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:27,280
You wrapped it this tight,

162
00:15:27,320 --> 00:15:28,800
will it leave marks on my leg?

163
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:30,880
I need my legs for work tomorrow.

164
00:15:30,920 --> 00:15:32,440
What kind of work?

165
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:34,720
What work?

166
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,440
You know what I do for a living.

167
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:39,400
How would I know?

168
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:41,320
This is literally our first day meeting.

169
00:15:44,320 --> 00:15:46,120
Look at my face carefully.

170
00:15:56,040 --> 00:15:58,040
Avoid putting weight on your foot.

171
00:15:58,720 --> 00:16:00,280
No high heels.

172
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:02,200
Otherwise your ankle could get worse.

173
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:04,720
You could even end up with vein problems.

174
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:06,920
- I…
- If there’s nothing else,

175
00:16:06,920 --> 00:16:08,200
I’ll excuse myself now.

176
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:10,240
Doctor, tomorrow I…

177
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:13,720
May.

178
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:16,040
Win.

179
00:16:17,320 --> 00:16:19,040
I knew you’d come, Win.

180
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:27,120
How are you?

181
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:33,440
The doctor said it’s just a mild ankle sprain.

182
00:16:36,640 --> 00:16:38,240
I’m glad you came, Win.

183
00:16:38,920 --> 00:16:40,840
Could you take me home?

184
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:43,040
There’s something I want to talk to you about.

185
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:47,320
- Well…
- Please, Win.

186
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:52,120
With my ankle like this,
I can’t drive myself home.

187
00:17:06,520 --> 00:17:08,720
Thanks for bringing me home, Win.

188
00:17:09,920 --> 00:17:12,240
Do you want to come in for a drink?

189
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:14,720
I’d rather not.

190
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:23,720
Hey.

191
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:25,720
Why aren’t you going home?

192
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:28,920
And… is that your bag?

193
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:33,040
I have nowhere to go.

194
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:34,520
Tonight,

195
00:18:34,520 --> 00:18:36,320
can I sleep in front of your house?

196
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:39,240
You’re not going to call the police on me, right?

197
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:47,520
Okay.

198
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:51,440
I’ll let you sleep inside the house tonight.

199
00:18:51,840 --> 00:18:53,440
But only for one night.

200
00:18:54,920 --> 00:18:56,040
Thank you.

201
00:19:04,440 --> 00:19:05,840
You’re burning up.

202
00:19:14,840 --> 00:19:17,520
Go change first.
I’ll get you some medicine.

203
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:38,400
Hey.

204
00:19:41,720 --> 00:19:42,720
Hey.

205
00:19:43,600 --> 00:19:44,840
Take your medicine first.

206
00:20:03,240 --> 00:20:04,520
Don’t fall asleep yet.

207
00:20:05,040 --> 00:20:06,520
Wake up and take the medicine first.

208
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,000
Hey.

209
00:21:35,240 --> 00:21:37,320
I don’t mean to pry or anything.

210
00:21:37,920 --> 00:21:40,920
I just want to know if you’re a scammer
or a sasaeng.

211
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:51,040
Rojanphanphong.

212
00:21:58,920 --> 00:22:01,240
Same last name as the real owner.

213
00:22:09,720 --> 00:22:11,320
This is already past the flight date.

214
00:22:37,840 --> 00:22:40,440
Or are you really the owner?

215
00:23:04,440 --> 00:23:05,720
What’s wrong?

216
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:08,040
Did you do something to me last night?

217
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:09,840
My bra…

218
00:23:09,920 --> 00:23:11,240
where did it go?

219
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:15,640
I’m not even wearing my underwear.

220
00:23:18,120 --> 00:23:19,240
Listen.

221
00:23:19,720 --> 00:23:22,800
I was just scared someone might get sick
and die in my house.

222
00:23:22,840 --> 00:23:24,640
So I changed your clothes for you.

223
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:26,200
From what I saw,

224
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:28,440
you look like a twelve-year-old.
There’s nothing there.

225
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:29,880
Hey, Win.

226
00:23:29,920 --> 00:23:31,120
Who said I don’t have any?

227
00:23:31,120 --> 00:23:32,920
I… do.

228
00:23:38,320 --> 00:23:39,520
Fine, you do.

229
00:23:42,320 --> 00:23:43,320
Hey…

230
00:23:43,360 --> 00:23:46,000
Do I really have to lose
my visual innocence to you?

231
00:23:47,720 --> 00:23:50,720
If my mom finds out, I’m so getting scolded.

232
00:23:51,520 --> 00:23:53,240
I’m definitely getting yelled at.

233
00:23:53,240 --> 00:23:55,240
Can you stop freaking out for a second?

234
00:23:56,920 --> 00:23:58,800
You’re talking this much,

235
00:23:59,320 --> 00:24:01,040
so clearly you’re not sick anymore.

236
00:24:01,520 --> 00:24:02,960
You’re fine now, right?

237
00:24:06,520 --> 00:24:07,520
Good.

238
00:24:08,120 --> 00:24:09,640
Then you can leave my house now.

239
00:24:12,520 --> 00:24:13,520
Please.

240
00:24:21,040 --> 00:24:23,040
Okay, okay, okay!

241
00:24:33,840 --> 00:24:34,920
Rice porridge.

242
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:43,160
Mmm… smells good.

243
00:24:47,920 --> 00:24:49,000
Wait, wait!

244
00:24:49,040 --> 00:24:50,440
Hey, what are you doing?

245
00:24:51,120 --> 00:24:52,200
My name is Wanneung.

246
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:55,440
Stop calling me “you.”
It feels weirdly distant.

247
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:57,800
We’re not close though.

248
00:24:57,800 --> 00:25:00,120
And how can you just eat my food like that?

249
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:02,600
Well, you made it for me, didn’t you?

250
00:25:02,640 --> 00:25:04,000
I saw there were two bowls.

251
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:05,600
See? I helped you eat already.

252
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:07,400
Come on, come eat with me.

253
00:25:07,440 --> 00:25:09,400
You’re actually pretty good at cooking.

254
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:10,600
You could open a restaurant.

255
00:25:10,640 --> 00:25:13,320
And the fish is super… fresh.

256
00:25:17,040 --> 00:25:18,920
Hey, aren’t you eating?

257
00:25:20,520 --> 00:25:22,320
Then… I’ll take the fish.

258
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:26,120
Just a little, okay?

259
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:40,720
Win.

260
00:25:40,800 --> 00:25:41,880
Have you seen the photos?

261
00:25:41,920 --> 00:25:43,840
There are leaked photos of you on X.

262
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:04,880
Hey.

263
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:08,200
If you’re done eating,
clean up and then leave my house.

264
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:28,720
Win Pawee cooked me breakfast.

265
00:26:28,840 --> 00:26:31,520
No one would believe that if I said it.

266
00:26:46,520 --> 00:26:49,120
Hope today’s a good day for you, Wanneung.

267
00:26:56,520 --> 00:26:58,720
Turn down all the reporters, Tom.

268
00:26:58,720 --> 00:27:00,840
I’m not doing interviews with anyone.

269
00:27:03,640 --> 00:27:04,720
Tom.

270
00:27:04,920 --> 00:27:08,320
Do whatever it takes
to get people off my back.

271
00:27:08,440 --> 00:27:10,040
I just want some peace.

272
00:27:12,640 --> 00:27:14,440
And don’t tell May either

273
00:27:14,520 --> 00:27:15,920
that I’m staying here.

274
00:27:18,320 --> 00:27:20,240
That’s all. Thanks so much.

275
00:27:22,120 --> 00:27:23,120
Hey.

276
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:26,600
