524
00:40:30,120 --> 00:40:31,520
You did listen, right?

525
00:40:32,120 --> 00:40:33,640
Are you done?

526
00:40:37,440 --> 00:40:38,480
So…

527
00:40:38,520 --> 00:40:39,600
That means…

528
00:40:39,640 --> 00:40:41,720
you’ll let me stay here now?

529
00:40:42,520 --> 00:40:43,800
I’m not a sasaeng.

530
00:40:43,840 --> 00:40:45,320
And I’m not a scammer either.

531
00:40:45,320 --> 00:40:47,400
I really am the owner of this house.

532
00:40:47,400 --> 00:40:48,800
You must’ve seen the photo…

533
00:40:48,840 --> 00:40:51,000
me standing in front of this house with my parents.

534
00:40:51,040 --> 00:40:53,840
I really lived here. I…

535
00:40:53,840 --> 00:40:55,640
Fine. You can stay.

536
00:40:55,720 --> 00:40:57,120
Really?

537
00:40:59,320 --> 00:41:01,400
Thank you so much.

538
00:41:01,440 --> 00:41:02,680
You’re seriously the nicest.

539
00:41:02,720 --> 00:41:04,640
You’re so pretty and…

540
00:41:04,640 --> 00:41:05,520
But…

541
00:41:05,520 --> 00:41:07,040
There’s a condition.

542
00:41:07,320 --> 00:41:09,520
A… condition?

543
00:41:19,400 --> 00:41:20,840
What are you doing, Win?

544
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:22,720
You can stay here,

545
00:41:22,920 --> 00:41:25,440
but we need to agree on the rules first.

546
00:41:26,520 --> 00:41:28,400
Sure, no problem.

547
00:41:28,440 --> 00:41:30,320
Go ahead, what is it?

548
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:32,800
Rule number one: no crossing boundaries.

549
00:41:32,800 --> 00:41:34,400
You stay in your space…

550
00:41:34,440 --> 00:41:37,120
I stay in my zone. You stay in yours.
No crossing lines.

551
00:41:37,440 --> 00:41:39,000
That includes my stuff.

552
00:41:39,040 --> 00:41:41,200
- You’re not allowed to use it.
- Stingy.

553
00:41:41,240 --> 00:41:43,640
And I know you’ve been sneaking food
from my fridge.

554
00:41:44,200 --> 00:41:45,480
Don’t let it happen again.

555
00:41:45,520 --> 00:41:47,000
So heartless.

556
00:41:47,040 --> 00:41:49,000
Rule number two: no mess.

557
00:41:49,000 --> 00:41:50,600
Anything you use in this house,

558
00:41:50,600 --> 00:41:52,000
put it back where it belongs.

559
00:41:52,040 --> 00:41:54,080
And don’t make things dirty.

560
00:41:54,120 --> 00:41:55,440
Relax, I’m a clean person.

561
00:41:55,480 --> 00:41:56,480
Rule number three:

562
00:41:56,520 --> 00:41:57,880
No loud noises.

563
00:41:57,920 --> 00:42:00,720
At all. I hate noise.

564
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:02,440
Rule number four:

565
00:42:03,120 --> 00:42:05,280
I wake up at six to work out.

566
00:42:05,280 --> 00:42:08,680
You have only two hours to use the kitchen
before I come back for breakfast.

567
00:42:08,720 --> 00:42:10,280
From ten to two,

568
00:42:10,320 --> 00:42:12,120
I need full focus for work.

569
00:42:12,120 --> 00:42:13,600
From six to eight,

570
00:42:13,640 --> 00:42:15,200
I watch the news.

571
00:42:15,240 --> 00:42:16,800
You shouldn’t touch the TV.

572
00:42:16,840 --> 00:42:19,080
Better yet, don’t even be
in the living room.

573
00:42:19,120 --> 00:42:20,680
I go to bed before ten.

574
00:42:20,720 --> 00:42:22,600
After that, do whatever you want.

575
00:42:22,640 --> 00:42:25,200
But whatever you do,
do NOT wake me up.

576
00:42:25,240 --> 00:42:26,320
Got it?

577
00:42:27,200 --> 00:42:28,600
I can’t remember all that.

578
00:42:28,640 --> 00:42:29,640
That’s fine.

579
00:42:32,200 --> 00:42:33,840
If you say you can’t remember,

580
00:42:34,440 --> 00:42:35,840
I’ll print it out for you.

581
00:42:36,720 --> 00:42:39,840
Wait, weren’t there only four rules?

582
00:42:40,040 --> 00:42:41,040
Yeah.

583
00:42:41,840 --> 00:42:44,000
Read them all and memorize them.

584
00:42:44,920 --> 00:42:47,040
Especially the last one.

585
00:42:48,120 --> 00:42:50,640
The fact that you’re living
in the same house as me…

586
00:42:50,720 --> 00:42:53,000
you’re not allowed to tell anyone.

587
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:54,520
Keep it a secret.

588
00:42:54,720 --> 00:42:56,800
Like I’d ever want to talk about you.

589
00:42:56,800 --> 00:42:58,600
That’s all, right?

590
00:42:58,640 --> 00:43:00,040
Just survive this first.

591
00:43:00,520 --> 00:43:03,000
How hard could it be?

592
00:43:03,040 --> 00:43:05,640
Rule number one: no crossing lines.

593
00:43:15,520 --> 00:43:16,680
Rule number three:

594
00:43:16,720 --> 00:43:19,520
No loud noises. At all.

595
00:43:28,520 --> 00:43:29,840
You’re stepping on the line.

596
00:43:31,520 --> 00:43:34,120
If I don’t cross it,
how am I supposed to get to my room?

597
00:43:34,440 --> 00:43:35,440
You’ve got five seconds.

598
00:43:35,640 --> 00:43:36,720
Five…

599
00:43:36,720 --> 00:43:37,720
Four…

600
00:43:37,760 --> 00:43:38,800
Three…

601
00:43:38,840 --> 00:43:39,920
Two…

602
00:44:37,920 --> 00:44:40,040
Why are you so mean?

603
00:45:05,920 --> 00:45:07,400
Hello, Tom. What’s up?

604
00:45:07,440 --> 00:45:09,120
Remember what May said in that interview?

605
00:45:09,440 --> 00:45:10,640
About…

606
00:45:10,920 --> 00:45:12,640
you coming back to work in the industry?

607
00:45:13,800 --> 00:45:14,880
Yeah.

608
00:45:14,920 --> 00:45:16,040
Why?

609
00:45:16,840 --> 00:45:18,520
But that’s not true.

610
00:45:18,920 --> 00:45:21,640
I never planned on coming back.

611
00:45:22,440 --> 00:45:24,520
May had the team send you a script,

612
00:45:24,920 --> 00:45:27,040
and wants you to meet the director.

613
00:45:29,640 --> 00:45:31,720
Tom, I’m not interested.

614
00:45:31,840 --> 00:45:33,440
But I read the script.

615
00:45:33,640 --> 00:45:35,040
It’s really good.

616
00:45:35,520 --> 00:45:37,200
You should at least take a look.

617
00:45:37,320 --> 00:45:39,120
And if you blow up again,

618
00:45:39,320 --> 00:45:41,080
it’ll help clear that clip scandal.

619
00:45:41,120 --> 00:45:42,920
That’s enough, Tom. I’m sleepy.

620
00:46:43,120 --> 00:46:45,000
I ran out of mine.

621
00:46:45,040 --> 00:46:47,480
So I borrowed yours to eat first.

622
00:46:47,520 --> 00:46:50,240
But I’ll buy some and pay you back.

623
00:46:52,320 --> 00:46:56,240
Sorry. I really will replace it, I promise.

624
00:47:10,400 --> 00:47:11,640
What are you doing?

625
00:47:15,440 --> 00:47:17,640
Can you help me take a look?

626
00:47:25,520 --> 00:47:27,840
No…don’t. Don’t come closer.

627
00:47:28,440 --> 00:47:30,200
Don’t…don’t mess with me.

628
00:47:30,240 --> 00:47:31,640
Or I’ll…

629
00:47:32,720 --> 00:47:34,520
Don’t touch me.

630
00:47:40,320 --> 00:47:41,840
So, Win Pawee?

631
00:47:42,440 --> 00:47:43,480
Shocked, right?

632
00:47:43,520 --> 00:47:46,040
Because my acting is that good, huh?

633
00:47:46,320 --> 00:47:48,520
I’m going to an ad casting today.

634
00:47:48,520 --> 00:47:49,920
After seeing that performance,

635
00:47:49,920 --> 00:47:52,640
you think I’ll totally get the job, right?

636
00:47:55,640 --> 00:47:57,120
If you do,

637
00:47:57,520 --> 00:47:59,120
I’ll make you grilled pork.

638
00:47:59,720 --> 00:48:01,480
You’re so nice.

639
00:48:01,520 --> 00:48:04,400
Then I want lots of pork belly.

640
00:48:04,440 --> 00:48:07,720
Bacon too…shrimp, shellfish, crab, fish. All of it.

641
00:48:08,320 --> 00:48:09,440
Deal.

642
00:48:10,320 --> 00:48:12,840
But if you don’t get it, no food.

643
00:48:13,320 --> 00:48:15,240
And you pay this month’s electricity bill.

644
00:48:17,240 --> 00:48:18,440
Okay?

645
00:48:20,840 --> 00:48:21,840
Okay.

646
00:48:22,320 --> 00:48:23,320
Deal.

647
00:48:23,840 --> 00:48:26,200
Grilled pork! Grilled pork!

648
00:48:26,240 --> 00:48:30,480
Grilled pork! Grilled pork!

649
00:48:30,520 --> 00:48:32,280
Grilled pork! Grilled pork!

650
00:48:32,320 --> 00:48:34,280
Grilled pork…wow, grilled pork!

651
00:48:34,320 --> 00:48:37,720
I really want grilled pork right now!

652
00:49:07,040 --> 00:49:09,120
Hey, you’re back already?

653
00:49:09,400 --> 00:49:10,840
How was it? Did you get the job?

654
00:49:11,000 --> 00:49:12,520
So we can have grilled pork together?

655
00:49:13,520 --> 00:49:14,720
I’m not hungry.

656
00:49:27,520 --> 00:49:29,320
It’s burning nicely.

657
00:49:31,920 --> 00:49:35,240
Crispy bacon, spicy dipping sauce.

658
00:49:46,240 --> 00:49:47,320
Win…

659
00:49:48,920 --> 00:49:50,600
There’s a small bowl in the cabinet.

660
00:49:50,600 --> 00:49:53,840
Grill some pork, drizzle sauce on it,
and put it by the stairs for me.

661
00:49:53,920 --> 00:49:55,840
Third step, okay?

662
00:49:57,400 --> 00:49:58,440
Why?

663
00:49:58,800 --> 00:50:00,240
Well, earlier someone came…

664
00:50:02,400 --> 00:50:03,720
Should I say this nicely?

665
00:50:05,440 --> 00:50:08,200
Listen…earlier the kid told me they were hungry,

666
00:50:08,200 --> 00:50:12,120
wanted some too, 
but you didn’t share any grilled pork.

667
00:50:12,520 --> 00:50:14,440
Kid! What kid?

668
00:50:15,040 --> 00:50:16,480
I never told you?

669
00:50:16,520 --> 00:50:18,720
I kind of keep a kid in this house…

670
00:50:18,840 --> 00:50:20,400
but they’re a child ghost.

671
00:50:20,440 --> 00:50:21,800
Not scary though.

672
00:50:21,840 --> 00:50:24,680
Now that you know, remember to
share food and snacks with them too.

673
00:50:24,720 --> 00:50:26,320
I’m heading out. Thanks, okay?

674
00:50:27,400 --> 00:50:28,600
You.

675
00:50:28,640 --> 00:50:29,920
You again.

676
00:50:50,120 --> 00:50:51,320
Wanneung.

677
00:50:52,640 --> 00:50:54,040
Wanneung.

678
00:50:55,920 --> 00:50:57,440
Wanneung.

679
00:50:59,720 --> 00:51:01,040
Wanneung.

680
00:51:02,440 --> 00:51:03,640
Wanneung.

681
00:51:04,120 --> 00:51:05,440
Wanneung.

682
00:51:07,520 --> 00:51:10,240
Win, what do you want?

683
00:51:10,840 --> 00:51:13,520
The power’s out. I can’t sleep.
Let me sleep here.

684
00:51:16,520 --> 00:51:17,520
You.

685
00:51:29,720 --> 00:51:31,920
What’s your problem?

686
00:53:19,280 --> 00:53:21,440
I’m about to become a star.

687
00:53:21,480 --> 00:53:23,560
Someone wants me to sign
with their agency.

688
00:53:23,600 --> 00:53:26,080
I’m excited. Don’t you get it?

689
00:53:26,080 --> 00:53:28,560
Growing up all by yourself,

690
00:53:28,600 --> 00:53:29,960
do you know what that’s like?

691
00:53:30,000 --> 00:53:31,560
Do you even really want
to be a star?

692
00:53:31,600 --> 00:53:33,960
Why? My acting…

693
00:53:34,000 --> 00:53:35,560
what’s so bad about it?

694
00:53:35,560 --> 00:53:37,480
Everything. It’s terrible.

695
00:53:38,000 --> 00:53:40,040
Oh yeah? And you’re so great?

696
00:53:40,080 --> 00:53:41,360
Good acting

697
00:53:41,400 --> 00:53:44,640
isn’t just memorizing lines
or copying someone else.

698
00:53:44,680 --> 00:53:46,880
You have to act from the inside.

699
00:53:49,280 --> 00:53:51,800
Grilled pork! Grilled pork!
(Grilled pork)

700
00:53:52,200 --> 00:53:53,680
Grilled pork.

701
00:53:55,400 --> 00:53:56,400
(Tiny dolphin splash)

702
00:54:00,680 --> 00:54:03,480
(Non-stop take care)

703
00:54:04,600 --> 00:54:05,880
Go.

704
00:54:08,000 --> 00:54:09,000
(Shy already)

705
00:54:09,200 --> 00:54:10,200
(A discreet kiss?)

706
00:54:12,480 --> 00:54:13,480
Cut.

707
00:54:16,800 --> 00:54:18,560
Camera resolution.

708
00:54:18,680 --> 00:54:21,400
(Taking advantage of the chaos)
